          "Clustering",
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "240 undergraduate students",
          "1 Multimedia Fundamentals Course",
          "LMS logs",
          "Zimmerman’s SRL Model",
          "[Weekly Videos and Quizz scores, weekly Last Date of Access to Each Learning Activity]",
          "Data was anonimized and stored in a vector containing the information for the different weeks. ",
          "k-Means",
          "-",
          "3",
          "Regular Learners: Often follow lecturer advice, activity closely follows recommended learning pathway.\n\nIrregular or Selective Learners: They pick and choose which activities to partake in. \n\nLate Learners: Only access VLE closer to exam",
          "Students in 2022 were informed of successful and less successful learning pathways undertaken by their previous colleagues. And this translated into a noticeable behaviorable shift relative to previous years - which also translated into a noticeable improvement in the average performance of the students in this cohort. \n\n",
          "Clustering on this work is done for learning trajectories.",
          "No ablation study to determine importance of different features.\n\nData is accumulated weekly (not daily)\n\nDistance metric is not optimized"
        ]
      ],
